{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the centromere protein T (CENP-T). CENP-T is a component of the CENPA-NAC (nucleosome-associated) complex, which plays a central role in assembly of kinetochore proteins, mitotic progression and chromosome segregation [[cite:PUB00066486], [cite:PUB00044194]]. CENP-T and CENP-W form a complex that is directly involved in establishment of centromere chromatin structure coordinately with CENP-A [[cite:PUB00067766]].  Histone-fold-containing CENP-T-W and CENP-S-X complexes can form a stable CENP-T-W-S-X heterotetramer. Structural analysis of the CENP-T-W-S-X complex suggests that it can form a unique nucleosome-like structure to generate contacts with DNA [[cite:PUB00058268]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR46904" "CENTROMERE PROTEIN T"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Centromere protein T", "short" "CENP-T"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 9, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 843, "taxa" 2884, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1409, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1409, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 942}, "pathways" 27}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR028255", :literature {"PUB00066486" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Izuta H" "Ikeno M" "Suzuki N" "Tomonaga T" "Nozaki N" "Obuse C" "Kisu Y" "Goshima N" "Nomura F" "Nomura N" "Yoda K."], "ISO_journal" "Genes Cells", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2443.2006.00969.x", "medline_journal" "Genes Cells", "title" "Comprehensive analysis of the ICEN (Interphase Centromere Complex) components enriched in the CENP-A chromatin of human cells.", "year" 2006, "raw_pages" "673-84", "volume" "11", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 16716197}, "PUB00067766" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Hori T" "Amano M" "Suzuki A" "Backer CB" "Welbu